social_posts.post_text: Sometimes he says “Bus” or “Carter”. He gets SO EXCITED when he sees the school bus and his brother comes home. 🚌
Our boys, @dannyduncan. They’ll always be the reason for everything we do, and the greatest thing that’s ever happened to us. These kiddos have my whole heart, and I love being their mom.
Off he goes! My baby is walking.
Photo dump from a great weekend out with the fam.

I don’t remember last time I felt as happy or good about myself as I feel today. I’m beyond grateful for my hubby and close friends who’ve been there for me when I was struggling with my mental health (you know who you are). It’s been a journey, but I can see the light at the end of the tunnel, and I celebrated with a 2.2 mile run today during my lunch break.
I love my babies, but I don’t love going to car dealerships with them 😂
I love being their mom.
He’s such a good boy, and he loves sitting on my lap while I work. 🐶
I took my boys to a castle today! —Wishing my hubby could’ve been there, but he’s working out of state 👩‍👦‍👦🏰

Last month I had the “crazy” idea to run a 5K and I signed up for one (even though I had never ran before). I started walking/jogging every other day, and now I can run up to 3 miles. My race is in two weeks and I cannot wait!!! 🏃🏻‍♀️
Sometimes I don’t realize how fast it goes. (Axel man is 17months)
We’re so lucky to have you @dannyduncan.
Feeling really good lately, and enjoying my family so much 💕

Happy Valentine’s Day to the love of my life. 7 years celebrating with you and forever to go. This place will always mean so much to me because it’s where we had multiple date nights, and also where you proposed! I love you @dannyduncan

I did it. After 6 weeks of training, I ran my first 5K!

Official pictures from the race. First 5K, but not my last. I had so much fun! Now I’m giving my ankle time to heal, and then I will work on improving my time and running another 5 or 10K next! 🏃🏻‍♀️🏃🏻‍♀️🏃🏻‍♀️
We’re all very tired but so excited about his half marathon. He’ll do great! 🏃🏻‍♂️
Today Carter said he wants to do a race, too! Now I gotta find him a fun one. 🏃🏻‍♀️🏃🏻‍♂️🏃🏻‍♂️
I did it!!! I ran my first 10K (6.2miles) and I earned my Kolache at the end. Now let’s relax all day haha 😂🏃🏻‍♀️

I ran a 10K because it was a personal goal I wanted to accomplish, and it made me very happy when I did! I didn’t care if I wasn’t at my ideal weight yet, or if my pace was slower than most. It was very difficult, but I had fun and I finished it. Don’t let your fears or thoughts stop you from getting what you want. You can do it.🏃🏻‍♀️ #kolachefactoryrun
